This is a textbook case of **coverage-without-verification**. Every production method is called (→ 95% line coverage), but almost nothing is actually asserted. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 Critical — Assert-Free Tests (pass even if behavior is completely wrong)

### 1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)
Calls `AddProduct` but never verifies the product was stored. A no-op `Save()` implementation would pass.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(result);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result.Price);
```

### 2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 31)
Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price changed. The store could silently discard the update.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", updated.Name); // name should be preserved
```

### 3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38)
Calls `RemoveProduct` but never verifies the product is gone.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

### 4. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)
Calls `GetProductCount` on an **empty** catalog and doesn't even capture or assert the return value. Double failure: wrong setup + no assertion.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(2, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

### 5. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68)
Calls `ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m)` but never checks any price was actually reduced. A 10% discount on $9.99 should yield $8.991.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

### 6. `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 84)
Calls `ImportFromCsv` but never verifies any product was created from the CSV input.
```csharp
// FIX:
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var imported = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(imported);
