**Root cause**: Every test follows a "call-it-and-pray" pattern — the method is invoked (boosting coverage), but the result is either ignored or checked with the weakest possible assertion (`IsNotNull`). This gives 95% line coverage with near-0% behavioral coverage. A mutation testing tool (e.g., Stryker.NET) would show a very low mutation kill rate, accurately reflecting the true test strength.
